-- Israel’s CAL Among Groups Eying Cyprus Airways, Stockwatch Says
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-05-25T15:02:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/israel-s-cal-among-groups-eying-cyprus-airways-stockwatch-says.html
Three investor groups are interested
in acquiring a majority stake in  Cyprus Airways Ltd. (CAIR) , the
island’s state-run airline, Stockwatch  reported  today, citing
George Mavrocostas, the carrier’s chairman and chief executive.  They include Canada’s Triple Five, Lebanon’s Middle East
Airlines and Israel’s CAL Cargo Airlines Ltd, the financial web
site said, citing Andreas Pieridis, president of Cyprus
Airlines’ Synyka labor union.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
